post_text: Was a fun and busy weekend for many of our students and athletes at Pumpkin Days this weekend. Attention parents, if your child needs a sports physical here's an opportunity. 🏀🏈⚾️🥎🏐🏃‍♀️🏃‍♂️

Greenfield United Methodist Church is hosting a free medical clinic from 6 to 8 p.m. the first and third Tuesdays of each month with registration from 5:30-6 p.m. Services offered at the free clinic include illness or minor injury care, well child exams, school and sports physicals, employment physicals, limited chronic disease management, diabetes and blood glucose and high blood pressure testing.

post_text:
Congratulations to O-M's Zayden Rawlings on your award! 👏🍀🐾

Fifty Iowa 4-H members have been awarded 2020 state 4-H project area awards following the statewide recognition process, which was held virtually this year. 👏

Each award recipient was granted a $100 award from Glen and Mary Jo Mente of Ames and the Iowa 4-H Foundation.

4-H project areas are broad topics that members can explore on their own or with the mentorship of a 4-H leader or other caring adult. Project area award applicants were asked to explain how they’ve demonstrated exemplary leadership, communication and civic engagement through their exploration of a project area over a number of years. 🍀
#InspireKidsToDo #GrowIowa4H

post_text:
In order to keep our fans and players safe please keep the following things in mind.

- there will be no bleachers, you must bring a chair
- don't chase foul balls, players will get them
-if possible please have exact change when paying to get into the game
- there will be no concessions available
- keep in mind of social distancing and keep within your family unit
- absolutely no one but coaches and players allowed in the dugouts.

Baseball and softball shirts should be in Tuesday. If you still owe please get your money to Ms. Dejongh.

Thank you parents and fans for keeping these rules in mind so we can have a successful baseball and softball season.

Students may pick up their personal belongings from their classrooms, lockers, cubbies, and hallway on Tuesday, May 5th and Wednesday, May 6th based on the following schedule:

9-10 a.m. last names beginning with A-D
10-11 a.m. last names beginning with E-H
11 a.m.-12 p.m. last names beginning with I-L
12-1 p.m. last names beginning with M-P
1-2 p.m. last names beginning with Q-T
2-3 p.m.last names beginning with U-Z

Please enter through the EAST doors.

If you have any questions please call the school or contact Teresa Thompson at teresa.thompson@o-mschools.org

Cody Winkler was elected Southwest district FFA Sentinel
March 7 at District FFA Convention in Harlan Iowa. His term will be one year from last Saturday Congratulations Cody. It has been eighteen years since the last FFA member was a District officer and that was Mike Cooley junior.

Gavyn Abell did an outstanding job giving the FFA creed at District Creed Speaking Contest last Saturday. He will advance giving the creed at state competition during the state FFA convention in Ames.

Congratulations Cody and Gavyn! 👏🐾
